Exploring Median Household Incomes in the U.S.

To begin, we visualized the median household incomes (for individual census tracts) using a histogram. Additionally, we placed a probability density graph (i.e., for the normal distribution) over the histogram. From this visualization, it becomes clear that median household incomes do not fall within the normal distribution.
